cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper proposes a deep learning-based method for photometric stereo, which is a computer vision problem related to shape recovery from multiple images taken under different lighting conditions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also heavily relies on deep learning techniques, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. The method proposed in the paper is based on a two-stage deep learning architecture, which involves intermediate supervision, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category. The paper also deals with shape recovery, which is related to graphics and visualization, so cs.GR (Computer Graphics) is another possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a method that can be applied to robotics and automation, so cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible category.
